results.name: Expansion of Product_{k>=1} 1/(1 - x^(2*k+1))^(2*k+1).
link: Vaclav Kotesovec, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000
Vaclav Kotesovec, A method of finding the asymptotics of q-series based on the convolution of generating functions, arXiv:1509.08708 [math.CO], Sep 30 2015
formula: a(n) ~ A * Zeta(3)^(17/36) * exp(-1/12 + 3 * Zeta(3)^(1/3) * n^(2/3)/2) / (2^(2/3) * sqrt(3*Pi) * n^(35/36)), where Zeta(3) = A002117 and A = A074962 is the Glaisher-Kinkelin constant.
results.author: _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Oct 12 2015
